ory: George Neville came to VA in or <i>c.</i> 1700 and settled on the headwaters of the Occoquan River, acquiring a large estate. His descendants, bearing the surnames Neville and Craig, were of considerable importance in Pittsburgh, PA, and Cincinnati, OH."],"variants":[{"name":"Nevells","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Neville  ."]},{"name":"Nevils","meanings":["English: variant of   Neville  ."]},{"name":"Novel","meanings":["English: variant of   Neville  .","Catalan: variant of   Novell  ."]},{"name":"Newell","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Neville  .","English: variant of   Noel  .","English: variant of   Newhall  ."]},{"name":"Nevills","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Neville  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Nevil","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Neville  ."]},{"name":"Newill","meanings":["English and Irish (or Norman origin): variant of   Neville  ."]},{"name":"Nevill","meanings":["English and Irish: of Norman origin, a variant of   Neville  ."]},{"name":"Nevels","meanings":["English and Scottish (Wigtownshire): of Norman origin, a variant of   Neville  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This surname is now rare in Britain.","Dutch and North German: unexplained."]},{"name":"Nee","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Dermot, John Patrick.","Irish (Galway): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Niadh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Nia</i>’ or <b>Mac Niadh</b> ‘son of <i>Nia</i>’. Compare   McNee  .   Needham   2 and   Neville   have also been adopted as Anglicized forms of this name.","North German: possibly a relationship name from Middle Low German <i>neve</i> ‘nephew, grand-child’."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Walter Neville was born on 31 May 1345, in Henham, Essex, England, United Kingdom. He married Lady Alianora de Dagworth on 23 June 1362, in Henham, Essex, England, United Kingdom. He died on 26 September 1386, in Galicia, Spain, at the age of 41."},"et":{"31 MAY 1345–26 SEP 1386":"31. mai 1345–26. september 1386","1345–1375":"1345–1375","1346–1375":"1346–1375","1368–1406":"1368–1406","1345–1386":"1345–1386","23 Jun 1362":"23. juuni 1362","29 November 1375":"29. november 1375","1368":"1368","1346":"1346","31 MAY 1345":"31. mai 1345","1345":"1345","5 September 1368":"5. september 1368","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","26 SEP 1386":"26. september 1386","1406":"1406","Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, England","Manor of Vachery, Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oronse, Galicia, Spain":"Galicia, Hispaania","Great Dunmow, Essex, England":"Great Dunmow, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"31 MAY 1345–26 SEP 1386":"31. toukokuuta 1345–26. syyskuuta 1386","1345–1375":"1345–1375","1346–1375":"1346–1375","1368–1406":"1368–1406","1345–1386":"1345–1386","23 Jun 1362":"23. kesäkuuta 1362","29 November 1375":"29. marraskuuta 1375","1368":"1368","1346":"1346","31 MAY 1345":"31. toukokuuta 1345","1345":"1345","5 September 1368":"5. syyskuuta 1368","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","26 SEP 1386":"26. syyskuuta 1386","1406":"1406","Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, England","Manor of Vachery, Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Oronse, Galicia, Spain":"Galici